==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: monacid
<hw>mon*ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mon-</ets> +
<ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having one hydrogen atom
replaceable by an acidic atom or radical.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> monoacid, monoacidic, monacidic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of neutralizing one equivalent of a
monobasic acid; -- said of bases, and of certain metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>monacid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: monacid
<hw>mon*ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An acid having one replaceable hydrogen atom.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> monoacid.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monad</ent>⟦br⟧
